            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Yes. ED is usually treatable, and even when natural intercourse stays difficult, IUI or IVF with ICSI offer reliable routes to pregnancy."
              },
              "name": "Can I father a child if I have erectile dysfunction?"
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Often a combination of physical causes (diabetes, blood pressure, hormones, blood-flow problems) and psychological ones such as stress and anxiety."
              },
              "name": "What causes erectile dysfunction?"
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "In most men, yes — through lifestyle changes, treating the underlying cause, medical therapy and counselling where needed."
              },
              "name": "Is erectile dysfunction treatable?"
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Completely. ED is a common medical condition and is handled with full privacy and sensitivity."
              },
              "name": "Is the consultation confidential?"
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "If collecting a sperm sample or timed intercourse is difficult, our team arranges supportive options so treatment can proceed smoothly."
              },
              "name": "How does ED affect fertility treatment?"
